# No Cloudscape in New Code

All **new** pages, components, and features must use **MUI** (`@mui/material`, `@mui/x-charts`), not Cloudscape.

## Rules

- **Never** import from `@cloudscape-design/*` in new files
- **Never** add new Cloudscape imports to existing files when building new features
- Use `@mui/material` for layout, inputs, navigation, feedback (Box, Grid, Card, Tabs, TextField, Typography, Table, Alert, Button, etc.)
- Use `@mui/x-charts` for data visualization (LineChart, BarChart, PieChart)
- Existing pages may keep their current Cloudscape imports (migration is a separate effort)

## Examples

```tsx
// BAD -- new code using Cloudscape
import { Container, Header, SpaceBetween } from "@cloudscape-design/components";

// GOOD -- new code using MUI
import { Box, Card, CardContent, Typography, Stack } from "@mui/material";
import { LineChart } from "@mui/x-charts/LineChart";
```
